Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees and boil a large #pot{} of water. Peel your @apple{2}, discard the skin and cut the apple from its core. Dice the apple up very finely. Lastly, cut the bottom centimetre from your @Tenderstem® broccoli{2} and discard these leftover dry ends.

Cook your apples in a small #non-stick pan{} on medium-low heat with @Netherend butter salted{1%tsp}, @water{5%tbsp}, @ground cinnamon{1/2%tsp}, @?sugar{1%tsp} and @salt{pinch} for ~{20%mins}. Put a lid on and stir, add a dash of water occasionally if you need to.

Cook your @new potatoes{4} in the boiling water with @salt{1/4%tsp} for around ~{15%mins}, or until you can easily slip a knife through them. 3 mins before they are done we'll add in the broccoli, but don't worry as we'll remind you about that later.

Rub @olive oil{1/2%tsp} over each @pork chops{4} and season them with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook in a non-stick pan on searingly high heat for ~{1%minute} on each side and ~{1%minute} standing on its rind (for a nice crisp edge).

> Tip: You may be best to cook the chops 2 at a time.

Transfer the chops to a #baking tray{} and scatter a few @rosemary{5%sprigs} across the top. Keep a sprig for your potatoes. Cook in the oven on the middle shelf for ~{12%mins}, which should make them nice and juicy inside. Remove them from the oven and rest them for a few mins.

Here's that reminder: 3 mins before the potatoes are done, put your broccoli into the water. Once 3 mins are up, you can drain both the potatoes and the broccoli, then separate.

Crush your potatoes ever so slightly using the back of a #fork{}. Fry these off in a non-stick pan on high heat with @olive oil{1%tbsp} and a tsp of @rosemary leaves{1%tsp}. Once the potatoes have crisped up around the edges, they are ready.

Serve with a big smile and a bigger appetite.